[{"id":"VR860310","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What must the magnitude of the electric field be in Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>2</mn> </math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR860310_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, a positively charged particle is moving to the right with initial speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <msub> <mi>v</mi> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </math></span></span> when it enters a region with uniform magnetic and electric fields, as shown. The magnetic field has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> and is directed out of the page, and the electric field has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>E</mi></math></span></span> and is directed toward the top of the page. The particle continues moving in a straight line through the region. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> (not shown), the magnitude of the magnetic field is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 B\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2 B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>, and the same particle begins with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and again continues moving in a straight line through the region.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a particle and a region that contains a uniform magnetic field and an electric field. The magnetic field has magnitude B and is directed out of the page, and the electric field has magnitude E and is directed toward the top of the page. The particle is moving at speed v sub 0 horizontally to the right toward the region of the magnetic and electric fields.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR860310.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction E over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction E over 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>E</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 E\"><math alttext=\"2 E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>E</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 E\"><math alttext=\"4 E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>E</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]